task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 20°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: To estimate the building's height, I need to see both its base and roof; adjusting pitch upward will reveal the full vertical structure from the current ground-level view.
I need to see both the base and roof of the building to estimate height; lowering the pitch from 30°UP to 0° will reveal the ground level while keeping the structure in view.
Adjusting pitch from 30° down to 0° will center the view to capture both the building's base and roof for accurate height estimation.
I need to center the view at 0° pitch to simultaneously see the building's base and roof for accurate height estimation, as previous adjustments showed oscillation between upper and lower sections.
The building's base and roof are now visible at 0° pitch after oscillating between up/down views, allowing height estimation using standard architectural proportions for a multi-story structure.
